org.bsc.bean
Class BeanDescriptorEntity

java.lang.Object
  java.beans.FeatureDescriptor
      java.beans.BeanDescriptor
          org.bsc.bean.BeanDescriptorEntity

public class BeanDescriptorEntity
extends java.beans.BeanDescriptor

BeanDescriptor extension for manage DataBase entity (TABLE,VIEW,STORED) and relations 

 example:
 
 BeanDescriptorEntity _entity = new BeanDescriptorEntity(class name);
 _entity.setEntityName("entity name");
 
 //  create join relation 
 
 _entity.createJoinRelation( "entity in relation", 
                                                                        new JoinCondition("fieldA","fieldB"), 
                                                                        new JoinCondition("fieldA","fieldC") );
 OR
 _entity.createJoinRelation( "entity in relation", 
                                                                        RIGHT_JOIN,
                                                                        new JoinCondition("fieldA","fieldB"), 
                                                                        new JoinCondition("fieldA","fieldC") );

Version:
2.2.0
Author:
Bartolomeo Sorrentino

set an additional identity where conditions used in all find commands 
 note:

 the condition string must contains fields like tableName.fieldName
 that are evaluated through constant expression

setCustomFindCommand

public void setCustomFindCommand(java.lang.String key,
                                 java.lang.String command)
add a new custom find command 
 Writing SQL command you can use the BeanManager build-in parameter listed below:
 {0} --> list of parameter
 {1} --> entity name
 {2} --> join conditions ( contains SQL JOIN clause too )
 {3} --> where condition


 Example:

 bd.setCustomFindCommand( "find100", "SELECT {0} FROM {1} WHERE {3} LIMIT 100" );
 bd.setCustomFindCommand( "find200", "SELECT {0} FROM {1} WHERE {3} LIMIT 200" );

 bd.setCustomFindCommand( "find200", "SELECT {0},MAX(x) FROM {1} {2} WHERE {3} GROUP BY x" );

Parameters:
key - commad key
command - SQL command
